{"article_id":"kNhM4S5t5fa95QSf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Deirdre Shesgreen and Nicole Gaudiano and Deborah Barfield Berry and Eliza Collins","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"WAS","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"INGTON -","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"t began Thursday as an emotionally charged Senate hearing","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"ith Christine Blasey Ford offering gripping testimony","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"hat rallied congressional Democrats to her side .","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"t ended with a fiery , passionate defense from Brett Kavanaugh","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"hat cemented Republican support for their embattled Supreme Court nominee .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"fter more than seven hours of questions and answers , heated rhetoric and tearful recollections , not one senator said publicly","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"hey had changed their mind about Kavanaugh 's bid","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"o sit on the nation 's highest court .","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"nd most lawmakers on the fence","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"specifically just a handful of moderates in each party -","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"tayed there , at least for now .","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"nly one , Sen. Bob Corker , R-Tenn. , announced his decision .","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"oth Ford and Kavanaugh were `` compelling , ''","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"ut the nominee `` deserves the presumption of innocence ''","depth":14},{"id":17,"text":"nd he 's qualified for the lifetime appointment ,","depth":14},{"id":18,"text":"orker said .","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"ther wavering senators ,","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"ncluding Republicans Susan Collins of Maine and Jeff Flake of Arizona ,","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"old Kavanaugh ' s fate in their hands .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"hey stayed mostly mum on Thursday ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"ith several going out of their way","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"o avoid reporters","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"tationed across the Capitol .","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"lake , a member of the committee , gave no hint of his leanings","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"nd asked no questions at the hearing .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"nstead , he described the committee as a group of 21 `` imperfect '' individuals ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"nd said","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"hat the two witnesses ' conflicting accounts left considerable doubt .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"thers lawmakers in Washington absorbed the bruising hearing","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"nd then retreated to their partisan camps .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"enate Democrats escalated their demands for an FBI investigation and a delay in the nomination process .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"epublicans stuck to their collective message","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"hat the vote should be held as quickly","depth":16},{"id":36,"text":"s possible .","depth":16},{"id":37,"text":"` I think","depth":18},{"id":38,"text":"t ' s time","depth":19},{"id":39,"text":"o vote , ''","depth":19},{"id":40,"text":"en. John Cornyn , R-Texas , told reporters","depth":18},{"id":41,"text":"fter the marathon hearing ended .","depth":18},{"id":42,"text":"` The longer that the nomination remains open ,","depth":17},{"id":43,"text":"e know","depth":18},{"id":44,"text":"hat more and more of these scurrilous , anonymous and uncorroborated allegations will be made . ''","depth":18},{"id":45,"text":"f Ford 's testimony ,","depth":18},{"id":46,"text":"e added ,","depth":18},{"id":47,"text":"` I don ' t think","depth":18},{"id":48,"text":"hey ' ve met their burden of proof . '' `","depth":18},{"id":49,"text":"We believe her , ''","depth":17},{"id":50,"text":"en. Elizabeth Warren , D-Mass. , tweeted from the other side of the partisan divide .","depth":17},{"id":51,"text":"everal Democrats suggested","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"hat Kavanaugh 's combative testimony was in itself disqualifying .","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"Judge Kavanaugh exhibited temperament","depth":17},{"id":54,"text":"mericans do not want in fair judges , ''","depth":17},{"id":55,"text":"aid Sen. Sheldon Whitehouse , D-R.I.","depth":16},{"id":56,"text":"` He was discourteous ,","depth":16},{"id":57,"text":"ashing out at senators","depth":18},{"id":58,"text":"aising legitimate questions ,","depth":18},{"id":59,"text":"nd made unfounded conspiracy allegations about imagined plots by political enemies . ''","depth":17},{"id":60,"text":"enate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer , D-N.Y. , said","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"f Republicans are `` so certain of Judge Kavanaugh ' s story ,","depth":16},{"id":62,"text":"hey should immediately demand","depth":18},{"id":63,"text":"hat the White House order the FBI to reopen the background investigation ,","depth":18},{"id":64,"text":"nd hold off on a vote for several days","depth":18},{"id":65,"text":"o all the facts can come out . \"","depth":18},{"id":66,"text":"ouse Democrats also stepped into the fray ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"ven though they have no vote on the nomination and no real power","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"o influence the outcome .","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"pair of House Democrats asked President Donald Trump to withdraw the nomination altogether .","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"nd more than 60 House Democrats urged Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , to postpone a vote on Kavanaugh .","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"As a lifetime appointment to our nation ' s highest court is on the line ,","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"e implore you to abandon the artificial timeline","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"ou have created ,","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"upport these women","depth":17},{"id":75,"text":"ho have come forward ,","depth":17},{"id":76,"text":"nd do your duty to the American people","depth":17},{"id":77,"text":"y conducting a fair and balanced nomination process , \"","depth":17},{"id":78,"text":"he Democratic lawmakers said in a missive to McConnell .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"t was hyper-political end to an extraordinary day on Capitol Hill .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"t 10 a.m. , the riveting Senate hearing began to play in congressional offices , in hallways , in bathrooms","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"on cell phones , on computer screens , and on televisions .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"t also aired on Air Force One , with Fox News ' s coverage live","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"s President Donald Trump flew back to Washington from New York .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"rump later condemned Democrats","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"nd pressed for a quick vote on his nominee .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"` Democrats ' search and destroy strategy is disgraceful","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"nd this process has been a total sham and effort","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"o delay , obstruct , and resist , ''","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"rump tweeted .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"` The Senate must vote ! ''","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"n the hearing room , at least one Democratic lawmaker wept openly","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"s Ford delivered her account of sexual assault from more than three decades ago .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"thers expressed sympathy , support , and gratitude for Ford 's courage","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"n coming forward .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"epublican lawmakers initially remained somewhat muted ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"eclining to pass judgment on Ford","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"efore they heard from Kavanaugh .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"uring an early break in the hearing , Sen. John Kennedy , R-La. , drew his finger across his lips","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"o indicate","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"e would have nothing","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"o say .","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"` I ' m not going to comment on any aspects of this hearing","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"ntil it ' s completed , ''","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"aid Sen. Thom Tillis , R-N.C. ,","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"ho later declared","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"hat Kavanuagh had his vote .","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"ut Kavanaugh 's angry denials , as well as his tearful account of the threats and harassment against his family , seemed to unite and energize Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"` I don ' t know","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"ow you can listen to him","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"nd not realize","depth":16},{"id":111,"text":"hat he ' s what he says","depth":17},{"id":112,"text":"e is , \"","depth":17},{"id":113,"text":"atch said ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"dding","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"hat he believes","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"avanaugh will be confirmed .","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"en. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , called Ford `` a nice lady","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"ho has come forward","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"o tell a hard story","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"hat ' s uncorroborated . '' But that should not be enough","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"o derail Kavanaugh 's nomination ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"e said .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"e accused Democrats of trying to delay a vote until after the November election ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"hen control of the Senate is up for grabs .","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"` All","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"can say","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"s that we ' re 40-something days away from the election","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"nd their [ Democrats ' ] goal","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"not Miss Ford ' s goal -","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"s to lay this past the midterms","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"o they can win the Senate","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"nd never allow [ President ] Trump to fill the seat , \"","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"raham charged .","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"y Thursday evening , Senate GOP leaders said","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"he Judiciary Committee would vote on Kav